│ from inspection in the debugger we see: BestFactor.Width = <vscale x 2>,      │
│ LegacyVF.Width = <vscale x 4>. The IR shows a conditional branch with a       │
│ constant false condition in the loop header, and a latch PHI whose one        │
│ incoming edge (from the header directly to latch) is actually unreachable.    │
│ This is a simplification opportunity (constant-folded branch + dead incoming  │
│ edge). The VPlan construction can omit the dead conditional branch, reducing  │
│ cost for certain VFs. The legacy cost model, however, precomputes branch      │
│ costs uniformly (precomputeCosts adds all branch terminators except the       │
│ latch), and marks them skipped. Because planContainsAdditionalSimplifications │
│ filters out instructions that are marked skipped in CostCtx                   │
│ (SkipCostComputation), it fails to recognize that the conditional branch      │
│ eliminated from the VPlan is indeed an extra simplification—thus it returns   │
│ false.                                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ Function planContainsAdditionalSimplifications() (lines 7280-7324) collects   │
│ all underlying IR instructions represented by VPlan recipes, then scans       │
│ original loop instructions, treating any non-PHI that is neither represented  │
│ nor skipped for cost computation as evidence of additional simplifications.   │
│ The eliminated constant conditional branch was pre-costed and therefore added │
│ to SkipCostComputation, causing the predicate (!SeenInstrs.contains(&I) &&    │
│ !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true)) to be false, incorrectly hiding the   │
│ simplification. This leads to the assertion failure when cost models disagree │
│ for VF choice solely due to that simplification.                              │
│                                                                               │
│ Thus, the detection logic is too strict: it suppresses recognition of         │
│ simplifications for instructions that were costed (and then marked skipped)   │
│ but structurally removed by the VPlan. Specifically, constant-folded          │
│ conditional branches become absent from VPlan recipes yet are excluded by     │
│ skipCostComputation.                                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit LoopVectorize.cpp lines 7318-7322 inside                                 │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications. Add a special-case: if an original     │
│ instruction is a conditional BranchInst with a constant condition and it is   │
│ not in SeenInstrs (i.e., removed in the VPlan), we treat it as an additional  │
│ simplification regardless of skipCostComputation. This correctly identifies   │
│ simplifications from constant-folded control flow and prevents spurious       │
│ assertion failures.                                                           │
│                                                                               │
